cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of selection bias in social media data and proposes methods to correct for it. The paper focuses on predicting population health statistics from Twitter data, which falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SD). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques (cs.CL) to extract relevant information from the Twitter data. Additionally, the paper deals with statistical methods for data analysis (cs.CY) and machine learning techniques for prediction (cs.CR).
